Edition:
Quote:  In individual ailments, if the patient did not derive immediate relief from the medicine prescribed by the doctor, the patient and the family concluded that the failure to respond was due to the sickness being a Maori disease (mate Maori) and beyond the white doctor's skill.
Notes:  1949 Buck Coming of Maori 548 in 1981 Brooker et al. NZ Medicinal Plants 19


